text: A lollipop and tv, does it get any better?
Hey. Ssh, be quiet. Let's prank Alice.
I'll stick this fake hair under my arm.
This is going to be good. Come on.
Hi Alice.
Uh... that's an interesting look.
Have you heard of waxing?
Good idea, I can use this.
Wow, that really does the trick.
I think I'm going to throw up.
Got her!
Urgh, this is so boring.
Did you hear something? Oh my phone.
Hello? Hey. Can you do this?
Flip the crepe.
Whoa, I'm not ready for that level of responsibility.
No.. no way... I'll be right back.
What do I do? Here goes.
What happened?
Oh, so close.
Home run!
I've told you before, don't play with your food.
It does look good.
Very funny.
Give me that.
Pay attention.
Remove the crepe and flip the pan.
Wow, that's so easy. Can I try?
I'll lift the crepe out the pan.
And place the pan on top.
I did it. And now I can eat it.
Good job.
Lala, bababa.  Oh soda... bababa. Lalalala.
Oops.
Nooooo! Make it stop.
I did not expect that.
At least there's a few drops left.
Come on.
Well that's annoying.
At least there's another bottle.
Steady... take it easy.
Please don't soak me.
Wait. I have a better idea.
I can use that corn syrup.
I'll put a spoonful of the corn syrup into the soda.
That should do it.
I'll put the lid back on.
Make sure it's tight and give it a shake.
And then put it into the fridge to set.
I think it's ready.
Bababa, lalala.
I don't need to worry about it spraying everywhere.
Wow, look at that.
And it tastes delicious.
This is much better than regular soda.
Woohoo.
Hi girls. I'm just going to grab a drink.
This is a good song.
That's enough.
Ooh soda. Dancing is thirsty work.
Thanks. See you on the dance floor.
Ok... that was rude.
I'll just pour another drink.
Prefect. I'm looking forward to this.
I'll take that. Thanks. I really need this.
Seriously? I just want a soda.
Can I have one?
Me too.
Are you kidding me?
Hold on. I know how to fix this.
First I need this jug.
I'll fill it with soda.
I'm not finished yet.
I'll loosely fasten this zip tie.
Then I'll wrap it around the jug handle.
I need to squeeze the jug so the zip tie slips over it.
The zip tie rests on the spout.
Now I can fill three cups at once.
It saves so much time.
Guys, come get your soda.
Nice. Thanks Emma.
Let's party.
Time to get my groove on.
Not so fast. No food or drink allowed, I need to scan you.
Whoa, is that thing safe?
Ok, you can go in.
Huh! Stop! What's this?
Whoa!
Give me that. You know the rules.
She's good. But not that good.
She'll never spot me down here.
Ahem. Can I help you?
Uh... nice shoes.
You know the rules.
But there so unfair.
Get out of here.
What happened?
The security is so strict. We'll never get into the party.
It's ok. Have some ice cream.
I can't, I have a sore throat.
I can help with that. Take these lozenges.
Wait. I think I know how to get our snacks by security.
Remove the lozenges from the pack.
Next, get a bottle of soda and a glass.
Pour the soda into the glass.
Add some food colouring to the soda.
We don't want it looking like soda.
Then add a spoonful of gelatine.
Fill a pipette with the mixture.
Pipe the mixture into the lozenge pack.
Fill the pack up and then allow it to set.
Place a sheet of aluminium foil onto the pack and seal it.
Stop. Open the bag. What have got here?
Hmm. Throat lozenges? Ok.
You can go inside.
Yes, I made it.
I think I deserve this treat.
I mean, it's for my throat. Ha.
Mmm, so tasty.
Time for a healthy snack.
Mmm, a yummy banana. Just what I need.
That's weird. Where did it go?
Banana thief!
I was hungry.
Ok. Luckily there's another one. It does look good.
Don't even think about it.
Gimme.
Get back. Take this.
Aw, a salad. These are boring.
Sorry... wait. I'll be right back.
Take a fork and a pair of pliers.
Use the pliers to twist the fork tines.
Twist them so they are vertical.
Just like this.
I can use this to slice the banana into sections.
Now we can both enjoy it.
Help yourself.
Really? You're the best.
Nom, nom. nom.
Wow, Alice really likes bananas.
No way. That is so funny.
Urgh, this tastes horrible. It needs some sugar.
Wow, I did not expect that. It's hilarious.
Where's my drink?
Huh? It's just sugar.
My dentist is going to be so mad.
How much sugar did I put in it?
That is so annoying.
Although, I think I know how to fix this.
This empty peanut butter jar will be handy.
I'll pour the sugar into it.
Then I'll replace the lid.
Next, I need this screwdriver to punch a hole into the lid.
I'll move it around to make the hole bigger.
It needs to fit a straw.
That's better.
The perfect amount every time.
Where is she?
Oh, you made it.
It's so good to see you.
There's so much to tell you. So the party...
This pasta looks good.
Uh-huh, right.
He was so cute. Wait, let me get some spaghetti.
So where was I? Right, the party.
I couldn't believe he was wearing those clothes...
No way.
Uh... Emma.
It was so embarrassing.
Emma... your spaghetti. I think you need to pay attention.
But it was a great night.
Can you please look at your plate.
I need to do something.
You should totally come to the next party.
It was a shame you couldn't make it.
I need to teach Emma table manners.
I feel like a hair stylist.
We've definitely worked up an appetite with this video.
What's your best food trick? Let us know in the comments below.
